hpnicfIpx.name: hpnicfIpx
hpnicfIpx.description: This MIB defines management information used on products which support ipx protocol. It includes 4 parts: 1.ipx interface configuration group - This group contains configurable management information and statistic information on each interface. 2.rip group - Rip means route information protocol. This group contains configurable management information and route status and route statistic information. 3.sap group - Sap means service access group. This group contains all service information. 4.ipx statistics group - This group includes ipx statistic information on all interfaces.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

hpnicfIpxStatus.name: hpnicfIpxStatus
hpnicfIpxStatus.description: This object is used to enable or disable ipx globally.

hpnicfIpxIfConfigTable.name: hpnicfIpxIfConfigTable
hpnicfIpxIfConfigTable.description: Table of configurable management information on each interface.

hpnicfIpxIfConfigEntry.name: hpnicfIpxIfConfigEntry
hpnicfIpxIfConfigEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing management information about a single interface.

hpnicfIpxIfIndex.name: hpnicfIpxIfIndex
hpnicfIpxIfIndex.description: This variable uniquely identifies the interface to which the configurations are applied.

hpnicfIpxIfNetId.name: hpnicfIpxIfNetId
hpnicfIpxIfNetId.description: The network number of the IPX address of this interface.

hpnicfIpxIfNodeId.name: hpnicfIpxIfNodeId
hpnicfIpxIfNodeId.description: The node number of the IPX address of this interface.

hpnicfIpxIfSplitHorizon.name: hpnicfIpxIfSplitHorizon
hpnicfIpxIfSplitHorizon.description: This node is used to set the split horizon status. Its default value is 'enabled'. In this case, the interface which receives a message can't send this message from the same interface. This function can avoid route loop. But it is unused for point to point link. If it is set to 'disabled', split horizon is disable.

hpnicfIPxIfTick.name: hpnicfIPxIfTick
hpnicfIPxIfTick.description: This object is used to set this interface's delay time. It is counted by ticks which is 1/18 second. By default, the ethernet interface's delay time is 1 tick, asynchronous serial interface's delay time is 30 ticks, WAN interface's delay time is 6 ticks.

hpnicfIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.name: hpnicfIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly
hpnicfIpxIfUpdateChangeOnly.description: When this variable is set to 'enabled', updating change is on. And sap and rip will send updating packets periodically to avoid broadcast storm. Whereas updating change is off.

hpnicfIpxIfRipMtu.name: hpnicfIpxIfRipMtu
hpnicfIpxIfRipMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of RIP updating packets.

hpnicfIpxIfEncapsuleType.name: hpnicfIpxIfEncapsuleType
hpnicfIpxIfEncapsuleType.description: This node is used to define the encapsulating form of IPX packets. 'dot2' indicates the form is 802.2, while 'dot3' means 802.3. And 'snap' indicates the form is ethernet-snap. It takes effect only on ethernet interface, and the default value is 'dot3', while 'unkown' for other types of port.

hpnicfIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.name: hpnicfIpxIfNetbiosPropagation
hpnicfIpxIfNetbiosPropagation.description: This node is used to configure whether the current interface can forward broadcasting packets which IPX type is 20 used for NetBIOS.

hpnicfIpxIfSapStatus.name: hpnicfIpxIfSapStatus
hpnicfIpxIfSapStatus.description: The status of sap on the current interface. It is enabled when ipx is enabled on this interface.

hpnicfIpxIfSapMtu.name: hpnicfIpxIfSapMtu
hpnicfIpxIfSapMtu.description: This variable is used to define the max length of SAP refreshing packets.

hpnicfIpxIfGnsReply.name: hpnicfIpxIfGnsReply
hpnicfIpxIfGnsReply.description: This object is used to enable or disable the current interface to response the IPX GNS request.

hpnicfIpxIfRowStatus.name: hpnicfIpxIfRowStatus
hpnicfIpxIfRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hpnicfIpxRouteMultiplier.name: hpnicfIpxRouteMultiplier
hpnicfIpxRouteMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate Rip aging time of route information. The absolute aging time = (hpnicfIpxRouteMultiplier * hpnicfIpxRouteUpdateTimer).

hpnicfIpxRouteUpdateTimer.name: hpnicfIpxRouteUpdateTimer
hpnicfIpxRouteUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set rip updating time which is based on seconds

hpnicfIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.name: hpnicfIpxRouteImpRouteStatic
hpnicfIpxRouteImpRouteStatic.description: This object determines whether static route can be imported.

hpnicfIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.name: hpnicfIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths
hpnicfIpxRouteLoadBalancePaths.description: This object defines the max equivalent paths to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes out of the new value will be set inactive.

hpnicfIpxRouteMaxResPaths.name: hpnicfIpxRouteMaxResPaths
hpnicfIpxRouteMaxResPaths.description: This object defines the max dynamic routes to the same destination. If the newly defined value is smaller than the current value, the routes will not be deleted until they age out or are deleted manually.

hpnicfIpxRouteTable.name: hpnicfIpxRouteTable
hpnicfIpxRouteTable.description: This table contains all dynamic and direct ipx route information of this system. The information of this table is read only.

hpnicfIpxRouteEntry.name: hpnicfIpxRouteEntry
hpnicfIpxRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes a dynamic or direct route.

hpnicfIpxRouteIndex.name: hpnicfIpxRouteIndex
hpnicfIpxRouteIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a route.

hpnicfIpxRouteDestNetId.name: hpnicfIpxRouteDestNetId
hpnicfIpxRouteDestNetId.description: The destination network number of this route information, and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe.

hpnicfIpxRouteNextHop.name: hpnicfIpxRouteNextHop
hpnicfIpxRouteNextHop.description: The next hop of this route.

hpnicfIpxRoutePro.name: hpnicfIpxRoutePro
hpnicfIpxRoutePro.description: The protocol type of this route information.

hpnicfIpxRoutePre.name: hpnicfIpxRoutePre
hpnicfIpxRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. The direct route's preference is 0, and it can't be modified. Dynamic route's default preference is 100.

hpnicfIpxRouteTicks.name: hpnicfIpxRouteTicks
hpnicfIpxRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks, that the packet takes to reach the destination.

hpnicfIpxRouteHops.name: hpnicfIpxRouteHops
hpnicfIpxRouteHops.description: The object indicates the number of hops that the packet must be passed through to reach the destination.

hpnicfIpxRouteTime.name: hpnicfIpxRouteTime
hpnicfIpxRouteTime.description: The aging time of this route information. The aging time of static and interface route information is 0.

hpnicfIpxRouteOutInterface.name: hpnicfIpxRouteOutInterface
hpnicfIpxRouteOutInterface.description: The out interface of this route information.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTable.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTable
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTable.description: This table contains all static ipx route information of this system.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteEntry.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteEntry
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteEntry.description: Each entry includes one static route information.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteDestNetId
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteDestNetId.description: The index of Static Route Table. This object and hpnicfIpxStaticRouteNextHop uniquely identify a static route. The destination network number of this static route information,and its value ranges from 1 to 0xfffffffe. Note that the broadcast network number is 0xffffffff and is not allowed in IPX. The network number of 0xfffffffe would be considered to be the network number of default route.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteNextHop.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteNextHop
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteNextHop.description: The sub-index of Static Route Table. The next hop of this static route information.

hpnicfIpxStaticRoutePre.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRoutePre
hpnicfIpxStaticRoutePre.description: The preference of this route information. Static route's preference is 60, and it can be configured.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteOutIf.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteOutIf
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteOutIf.description: The out interface of this route. This interface can be serial or pos interface.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTicks.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTicks
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteTicks.description: The time, in ticks that the packet takes to reach the destination with the static route.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteHops.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteHops
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteHops.description: This object indicates how many hops are needed to arrive at the destination network.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteStatus.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteStatus
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteStatus.description: The status of this static route.

hpnicfIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.name: hpnicfIpxStaticRouteRowStatus
hpnicfIpxStaticRouteRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatTable.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatTable
hpnicfIpxRouteStatTable.description: A table includes all statistic route information.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatEntry.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatEntry
hpnicfIpxRouteStatEntry.description: An entry records a statistic information of route.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatPro.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatPro
hpnicfIpxRouteStatPro.description: The protocol type of the route information. The value of 'total' is the total amount of all kinds of IPX routes.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatRoutes.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatRoutes
hpnicfIpxRouteStatRoutes.description: The route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatActives.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatActives
hpnicfIpxRouteStatActives.description: The active route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatAddeds.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatAddeds
hpnicfIpxRouteStatAddeds.description: The added route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatDeleteds.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatDeleteds
hpnicfIpxRouteStatDeleteds.description: The deleted but not freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hpnicfIpxRouteStatFreeds.name: hpnicfIpxRouteStatFreeds
hpnicfIpxRouteStatFreeds.description: The freed route amount of the corresponding protocol type.

hpnicfIpxSapMultiplier.name: hpnicfIpxSapMultiplier
hpnicfIpxSapMultiplier.description: This node is used to calculate aging time of service information. The absolute aging time = (hpnicfIpxSapMultiplier * hpnicfIpxSapUpdateTimer).

hpnicfIpxSapUpdateTimer.name: hpnicfIpxSapUpdateTimer
hpnicfIpxSapUpdateTimer.description: This node is used to set service packet updating time which is based on seconds.

hpnicfIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.name: hpnicfIpxSapGnsLoadBalance
hpnicfIpxSapGnsLoadBalance.description: This object is used to set whether the system will reply to the GNS request with the Round-Robin way. By default, the system will response to the GNS request with the servers known to the device in turn, preventing from the nearest server's over loading. With value of disabled, in this way, the system will response to the request with the nearest server(who has smallest hop in system's service information table).

hpnicfIpxSapMaxResServers.name: hpnicfIpxSapMaxResServers
hpnicfIpxSapMaxResServers.description: This object is used to configure maximum number of servers of a type. If the newly defined value is smaller than the previous value, the information out of the value will not be deleted. If the queue reaches to the maximum number, no new information can be added.

hpnicfIpxServiceTable.name: hpnicfIpxServiceTable
hpnicfIpxServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all dynamic service information. The dynamic service information can be read only.

hpnicfIpxServiceIndex.name: hpnicfIpxServiceIndex
hpnicfIpxServiceIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a service information.

hpnicfIpxServiceNetId.name: hpnicfIpxServiceNetId
hpnicfIpxServiceNetId.description: The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hpnicfIpxServiceNodeId.name: hpnicfIpxServiceNodeId
hpnicfIpxServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hpnicfIpxServiceSocketNo.name: hpnicfIpxServiceSocketNo
hpnicfIpxServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service

hpnicfIpxServicePreference.name: hpnicfIpxServicePreference
hpnicfIpxServicePreference.description: The service preference of the service

hpnicfIpxServiceHops.name: hpnicfIpxServiceHops
hpnicfIpxServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

hpnicfIpxServiceRecvIf.name: hpnicfIpxServiceRecvIf
hpnicfIpxServiceRecvIf.description: Interface from which the service is receieved

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceTable.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceTable
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceTable.description: This table inlcudes all static service information. This table supports to creation and deletione of a static service, but not supports to modification

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceType.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceType
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceType.description: The index of static service table.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceName.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceName
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceName.description: The sub-index of static service table. The name of the service.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNetId.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNetId
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNetId.description: The sub-index of static service table. The IPX network number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNodeId.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNodeId
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceNodeId.description: The IPX node number portion of the IPX address of the service.

hpnicfIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.name: hpnicfIpxStatciServiceSocketNo
hpnicfIpxStatciServiceSocketNo.description: The socket portion of the IPX address of the service.

hpnicfIpxStaticServicePreference.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServicePreference
hpnicfIpxStaticServicePreference.description: The service preference of the server.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceHops.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceHops
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceHops.description: The hops from the device to the server.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceStatus.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceStatus
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceStatus.description: The status of the service that you created. The value of this object is determined by system.

hpnicfIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.name: hpnicfIpxStaticServiceRowStatus
hpnicfIpxStaticServiceRowStatus.description: The status of this row. To create a row, user can select 'createAndGo'. If the row is created successfully, this object will became 'active'. To delete one row, user can select 'destory' and the row will be deleted.

hpnicfIpxStatTotalReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStatTotalReceives
hpnicfIpxStatTotalReceives.description: The total number of packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatPitchs.name: hpnicfIpxStatPitchs
hpnicfIpxStatPitchs.description: The number of received packets filled by device when forwarding or delivering up to upper protocol.

hpnicfIpxStatLenErrors.name: hpnicfIpxStatLenErrors
hpnicfIpxStatLenErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to length error.

hpnicfIpxStatFormatErrors.name: hpnicfIpxStatFormatErrors
hpnicfIpxStatFormatErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to format error.

hpnicfIpxStatBadHops.name: hpnicfIpxStatBadHops
hpnicfIpxStatBadHops.description: The number of received packets which's value of field Hops is greater than 16.

hpnicfIpxStatHopsDiscards.name: hpnicfIpxStatHopsDiscards
hpnicfIpxStatHopsDiscards.description: The number of received packets of which hops portion is equal to 16.

hpnicfIpxStatOtherErrors.name: hpnicfIpxStatOtherErrors
hpnicfIpxStatOtherErrors.description: The number of received packets discarded due to other error.

hpnicfIpxStatLocalDests.name: hpnicfIpxStatLocalDests
hpnicfIpxStatLocalDests.description: The number of received packets which destination is the local device. Note that this would include the IPX NetBIOS propagation packets and those broadcast packets just to the network on which local device resides.

hpnicfIpxStatCantDeals.name: hpnicfIpxStatCantDeals
hpnicfIpxStatCantDeals.description: The number of received packets with which can't be dealt. One possible reason for discarding such a packet would be receiving a packet of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

hpnicfIpxStatForwards.name: hpnicfIpxStatForwards
hpnicfIpxStatForwards.description: The number of received packets to be forwarded in the case that the entity was not their final destination.

hpnicfIpxStatGenerates.name: hpnicfIpxStatGenerates
hpnicfIpxStatGenerates.description: The number of sent packets that the device generated itself.

hpnicfIpxStatNoRoutes.name: hpnicfIpxStatNoRoutes
hpnicfIpxStatNoRoutes.description: The number of packets discarded due to no route to the destination was found in routing table.

hpnicfIpxStatOutDiscards.name: hpnicfIpxStatOutDiscards
hpnicfIpxStatOutDiscards.description: The number of packets to be discarded when sending out. Note that this counter would not include the packet(s) discarded due to no route.

hpnicfIpxStatRipSends.name: hpnicfIpxStatRipSends
hpnicfIpxStatRipSends.description: The total number of RIP packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatRipReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStatRipReceives
hpnicfIpxStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received.

hpnicfIpxStaRipRspSends.name: hpnicfIpxStaRipRspSends
hpnicfIpxStaRipRspSends.description: The total number of RIP response packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStaRipRspReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStaRipRspReceives
hpnicfIpxStaRipRspReceives.description: The total number of RIP response packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatRipReqReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStatRipReqReceives
hpnicfIpxStatRipReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP request packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatRipReqDeals.description: The total number of RIP request packets dealt with.

hpnicfIpxStatRipReqSends.description: The total number of RIP request packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatRipPeriUpdates.name: hpnicfIpxStatRipPeriUpdates
hpnicfIpxStatRipPeriUpdates.description: The total number of periodic update RIP packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatSapGenReqReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStatSapGenReqReceives
hpnicfIpxStatSapGenReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP general request packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives.name: hpnicfIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives
hpnicfIpxStatSapSpecReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP specific request packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatSapGnsReqReceives.description: The total number of SAP GNS request packets received.

hpnicfIpxStatSapGenRspSends.description: The total number of SAP general response packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatSapSpecRspSends.description: The total number of SAP specific response packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatSapGnsRspSends.name: hpnicfIpxStatSapGnsRspSends
hpnicfIpxStatSapGnsRspSends.description: The total number of SAP GNS response packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatSapPeriUpdates.name: hpnicfIpxStatSapPeriUpdates
hpnicfIpxStatSapPeriUpdates.description: The total number of SAP periodic update packets sent.

hpnicfIpxStatSapInPktErrors.name: hpnicfIpxStatSapInPktErrors
hpnicfIpxStatSapInPktErrors.description: The total number of SAP error packets received.

hpnicfIpxIfStatTable.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatTable
hpnicfIpxIfStatTable.description: The table of the statistic information on each interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatEntry.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatEntry
hpnicfIpxIfStatEntry.description: The entry of the statistic table.

hpnicfIpxIfStatIndex.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatIndex
hpnicfIpxIfStatIndex.description: The index of the table's entry. According to the interface's index.

hpnicfIpxIfStatNetId.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatNetId
hpnicfIpxIfStatNetId.description: The network number of the IPX address of this interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatNodeId.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatNodeId
hpnicfIpxIfStatNodeId.description: The node number of the IPX address of this interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxReceives.name: hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxReceives
hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxReceives.description: The total number of packets received on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxSends.description: The total number of packets sent on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxRecvBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatIpxSendBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipReceives.description: The total number of RIP packets received on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipDiscards.description: The total number of RIP packets discarded on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipSpecReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP specific request packets received on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipSpecRspSends.description: The total number of RIP specific response packets sent on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipGenReqReceives.description: The total number of RIP general request packets received on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatRipGenRspSends.description: The total number of RIP general response packets sent on the interface.

hpnicfIpxIfStatSapReceives.description: The total number of SAP packets received on the interface.
